WEBVTT

00:07.875 --> 00:10.378
BUENOS DÍAS.

00:29.197 --> 00:31.099
THEY DIDN'T HAVE LOW-FAT.

00:31.132 --> 00:33.234
SO IT'S--
CREAM.

00:35.203 --> 00:37.105
THANKS.

00:37.138 --> 00:39.907
[ Grey ]
STILL NO TARGET.

00:42.876 --> 00:44.912
HE REMINDS ME OF SOMEONE.

00:46.114 --> 00:48.082
DOES HE?

00:48.116 --> 00:50.284
MY WIFE'S GRANDDAD MAYBE.

00:50.318 --> 00:52.386
WHAT'S THAT MAKE HIM?
MY GRANDFATHER-IN-LAW?

00:52.420 --> 00:55.389
YOUR GRANDFATHER-IN-LAW
EVER BOMB A BUSLOAD
OF SCHOOL CHILDREN?

00:55.423 --> 00:58.659
NOT THAT I KNOW OF.
THERE'S ONE
BIG DIFFERENCE THEN.

00:59.793 --> 01:01.929
GREY, YOU GOT 40 MINUTES
OF DOWNTIME.

01:01.962 --> 01:04.198
BOB, YOU GOT THE GUN.

01:04.232 --> 01:06.900
WILLIAMS, SCOPE.

01:13.307 --> 01:15.109
[ Sighs ]

01:20.080 --> 01:23.284
- I'LL BE, UH--
- I BELIEVE WE ALL KNOW
WHERE YOU'LL BE.

01:28.656 --> 01:32.226
[ Beeping ]

01:32.260 --> 01:34.362
[ Sighs ]

01:41.535 --> 01:43.904
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

01:43.937 --> 01:47.708
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

01:51.679 --> 01:54.315
[ Chattering Continues ]

01:55.216 --> 01:57.785
WHAT?

01:57.818 --> 01:59.687
IT'S OFF.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

01:59.720 --> 02:03.757
THE MISSION IS OFF.
I GOT NO SUCH ORDER.

02:03.791 --> 02:06.927
THIS IS YOUR ORDER.
HIS MAJESTY'S SPANISH GOVERNMENT
IS WITHDRAWING CONSENT.

02:06.960 --> 02:08.929
BECAUSE?
SOME POLITICOS,

02:08.962 --> 02:11.632
THEY'VE DECIDED THEY'D RATHER
TRADE HIM THAN KILL HIM.

02:11.665 --> 02:14.168
THIS HAS BECOME AN ILLEGAL
OPERATION. YOU UNDERSTAND?

02:14.202 --> 02:17.871
THIS ENTIRE COUNTRY IS NOW
A NONPERMISSIVE ENVIRONMENT.
GET OUT!

02:19.340 --> 02:22.876
- GET OUT NOW.
- [ Busy Signal Beeping ]

02:23.844 --> 02:26.214
[ Sighs ]

02:29.750 --> 02:32.520
[ Busy Signal Continues ]

02:36.257 --> 02:40.060
TARGET SPOTTED.
WHITE. INDIA. SEVEN.

02:40.093 --> 02:41.995
ROGER.

02:45.833 --> 02:48.602
- HE'S OUT OF THE LIGHT.
- YOU WANT TO SWITCH
TO NIGHTSCOPE?

02:58.379 --> 03:00.214
NO. HE'S BACK OUT.
I CAN SEE HIM.

03:01.549 --> 03:04.385
YELLOW. YELLOW.

03:04.418 --> 03:05.819
RED.

03:05.853 --> 03:07.921
WHO'S--
BANK PRESIDENT.

03:07.955 --> 03:11.158
[ Bob Sighs ]

03:11.191 --> 03:14.061
YELLOW.

03:20.634 --> 03:22.536
GREEN.
[ Gun Fires ]

03:24.405 --> 03:27.275
ALL RIGHT THEN.
RIGHTEOUS SHOT.

03:35.549 --> 03:37.217
PRAIRIE FIRE.

03:41.789 --> 03:44.325
LEAVE IT.

03:50.631 --> 03:53.267
PRAIRIE FIRE.
[ Sighs ]

03:56.570 --> 03:58.339
WHAT IS PRAIRIE FIRE?

04:01.642 --> 04:04.545
[ Jonas ]
DOWN THE ELEVATOR SHAFT.

04:04.578 --> 04:08.181
E&E PLAN IS IN EFFECT NOW.
FOLLOW YOUR SPECIFIC PORTIONS.
AIR.

04:09.783 --> 04:12.219
LAND. SEA.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.921
BOSS--

04:13.954 --> 04:16.357
ESCAPE AND EVADE, BROWN.
SEE YOU AROUND THE WATERCOOLER.

04:21.261 --> 04:25.165
[ Sirens Wailing ]

04:32.039 --> 04:34.274
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

04:34.308 --> 04:36.644
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

04:36.677 --> 04:39.112
* HERE WE GO
ON THE ROAD *

04:39.146 --> 04:41.248
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

04:41.281 --> 04:43.351
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

04:43.384 --> 04:46.286
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

04:56.330 --> 04:58.799
[ Glass Tinkles ]

05:03.704 --> 05:05.539
[ Door Shuts Quietly ]

05:57.024 --> 06:00.461
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

06:05.799 --> 06:07.935
[ Lock Beeps ]

06:09.637 --> 06:12.840
HEY! WHAT THE HELL?

06:12.873 --> 06:15.375
DO YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING?
THEY KNOW WHAT YOU LOOK LIKE.

06:15.409 --> 06:17.911
THEY HAVE ALL OF YOUR NAMES.
THEY WILL PUT YOU IN JAIL.

06:17.945 --> 06:21.081
AND I CAN'T HELP YOU NOW.
I MEAN, NOT ME,
NOT THE AGENCY.

06:21.114 --> 06:24.284
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
ARE YOU DEAF?

06:24.317 --> 06:27.187
WE HAVE NO CONNECTION
WITH YOU OR YOUR TEAM.

06:27.220 --> 06:30.791
YOU KNOW, I AM SURPRISED.
YOU DIDN'T OFFER US A LIFT HOME.

06:30.824 --> 06:32.760
LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU--
[ Grunts ]
[ Punch Lands ]

06:32.793 --> 06:35.896
[ Coughing ]

06:37.965 --> 06:39.967
[ Choking ]

06:42.470 --> 06:45.305
[ Shallow Breathing ]

06:51.479 --> 06:53.447
[ Breathing Fast ]

06:54.848 --> 06:58.486
[ Rattling ]

07:02.790 --> 07:05.158
[ Lock Turning ]

07:13.366 --> 07:15.603
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

07:15.636 --> 07:19.239
ARE YOU IN TROUBLE, CHILD?
I'M NOT IN TROUBLE.

07:19.272 --> 07:22.109
THEN, TO WHAT
DO WE OWE THE PLEASURE?

07:22.142 --> 07:24.077
I'LL TALK TO DADDY.
EXCUSE ME?

07:24.111 --> 07:26.580
I'LL TALK TO DADDY.
YOU'LL TALK TO YOUR MOTHER,
RIGHT NOW.

07:26.614 --> 07:29.617
- I DON'T THINK I WILL.
- YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHO STOLE MY DAUGHTER?

07:29.650 --> 07:32.152
OR HAS THAT SCHOOL
BEEN TEACHING YOU
THIS KIND OF OBSCENITY?

07:32.185 --> 07:33.987
I CAME FOR SOME PAPERS.

07:36.990 --> 07:39.760
- WHAT IS THIS?
- THAT'S A PISTOL.

07:39.793 --> 07:44.565
ARE YOU ON DRUGS
TO ACT LIKE THIS?
SIT DOWN, CHILD.

07:55.543 --> 07:58.011
AND YOU LISTEN
TO WHAT I HAVE TO SAY.

07:58.045 --> 08:00.848
I AM YOUR MOTHER.

08:00.881 --> 08:04.818
AND I LOVE YOU MORE THAN
ANYTHING ELSE IN THIS WORLD.

08:04.852 --> 08:07.855
I BROUGHT YOU INTO THIS WORLD,
AND I WILL TAKE YOU OUT...

08:07.888 --> 08:10.323
BEFORE I ALLOW YOU
ONE MORE MOMENT OF DISRESPECT.

08:10.357 --> 08:12.560
MY PROBLEM IS--
I KNOW WHAT YOUR PROBLEM IS!

08:12.593 --> 08:15.529
YOUR PROBLEM IS
YOU'VE LOST YOUR MIND!

08:15.563 --> 08:19.833
NOW, WHAT DID YOU
COME HOME FOR?

08:21.334 --> 08:23.671
I NEED SOME PAPERS.
THANK YOU.

08:23.704 --> 08:26.974
WHICH PAPERS DO YOU NEED, AND
WHAT DO YOU REQUIRE THEM FOR?

08:27.007 --> 08:29.610
I'M DROPPING OUT OF SCHOOL.

08:31.712 --> 08:35.182
MY FINE BLACK ASS,
YOU ARE.

08:35.215 --> 08:37.885
IT'S FREIGHT ONLY, SIR.

08:37.918 --> 08:39.987
WE'RE A CARGO CARRIER.

08:40.020 --> 08:42.322
WOULD YOU LOOK AT MY PASSPORT,
PLEASE?

08:42.355 --> 08:44.124
SIR, WE'RE A FREIGHT CARRIER.

08:45.593 --> 08:49.763
WOULD YOU LOOK AT MY PASSPORT,
PLEASE?

08:56.937 --> 08:58.972
MR. LARGO?

09:08.148 --> 09:09.950
HOLD THE PLANE.

09:09.983 --> 09:13.120
WELCOME ABOARD
LIBERTY CARGO, MR.--
THANK YOU.

09:19.727 --> 09:22.796
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

09:25.332 --> 09:27.735
[ Engine Running ]

09:28.769 --> 09:30.938
[ Engine Stops ]

09:40.648 --> 09:42.716
[ Man Speaking Spanish ]
NO.

09:42.750 --> 09:44.652
[ Speaking Spanish ]

09:50.624 --> 09:52.760
[ Shouting In Spanish ]

09:56.163 --> 09:58.265
¡CUIDADO!

10:06.640 --> 10:10.443
* [ Flamenco ]
[ Man Whistles ]

10:13.613 --> 10:16.116
¡VENGA!
[ Man Whistles ]

10:17.517 --> 10:20.821
[ Shouting In Spanish ]

10:26.193 --> 10:28.729
[ Speaking Spanish ]

10:29.863 --> 10:32.065
[ Speaking Spanish ]

10:35.368 --> 10:37.504
¿QUÉ PASA?

10:38.872 --> 10:42.910
[ Speaking Spanish ]

10:48.415 --> 10:50.918
* [ Flamenco Continues ]

11:10.237 --> 11:12.105
* [ Ends ]

11:14.274 --> 11:17.377
BUT THE PROBLEM IS
THE MEN TAKE ADVANTAGE.

11:17.410 --> 11:20.213
THEN WHAT'S THE POINT
OF DATING? WHAT'S THE POINT
IN GETTING MARRIED?

11:20.247 --> 11:23.350
THAT IS A GOOD QUESTION.
BUT THINGS CHANGE.

11:23.383 --> 11:25.753
THINK THERE'S ANY CHANCE YOU
AND BRIAN'LL GET BACK TOGETHER?

11:25.786 --> 11:27.755
NO. HE'S ALL OVER
THIS ANGELA GIRL.

11:27.788 --> 11:29.890
OH! THEN YOU'RE
WELL RID OF HIM.

11:29.923 --> 11:34.094
- DOESN'T FEEL THAT WAY.
- BETS, THERE'S LOTS OF BOYS
TO DATE AT COLLEGE.

11:34.127 --> 11:37.564
- JUST 'CAUSE ONE IS--
- THEY'RE ALL SNOOTY,
STUCK-UP SNOBS.

11:37.597 --> 11:40.333
ALL THEY WANT TO DO IS PARTY,
DRINK AND DO DRUGS.

11:40.367 --> 11:42.569
RUSH YOU, GIRL?

11:42.602 --> 11:46.206
YEAH. I WASN'T READY.
I--

11:46.239 --> 11:48.742
NO. IT'S GOOD, BETS.

11:48.776 --> 11:52.746
DON'T EVER LET ANYONE
RUSH YOU INTO SOMETHING
YOU'RE NOT READY FOR.

11:53.814 --> 11:55.783
YOU KNOW, YOU COULD
TELL YOUR MOM THAT.

11:55.816 --> 11:58.485
SHE'D UNDERSTAND.
NO, I CAN'T.

11:59.386 --> 12:02.189
[ Sighs ]

12:02.222 --> 12:04.091
MAYBE JUST NOT YET.

12:05.492 --> 12:08.695
IT'S GOOD TO HAVE YOU HOME.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.931
I KNOW YOUR MOTHER
FEELS THE SAME WAY.

12:10.964 --> 12:13.000
AUNT TIFFY?

12:14.935 --> 12:16.970
HOW LONG DOES IT TAKE
TO GET OVER HIM?

12:18.105 --> 12:20.507
FOREVER.

12:27.080 --> 12:28.849
[ Sighs ]

12:31.584 --> 12:33.620
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

12:42.595 --> 12:44.798
[ Shouting ]

12:51.338 --> 12:53.340
[ Woman ]
HE WENT THAT WAY!

12:53.373 --> 12:56.609
[ Shouting In Spanish ]

12:58.211 --> 12:59.947
[ Shouting In Spanish ]

13:08.788 --> 13:11.691
SERENA, MOMMY'S COMING.

13:11.724 --> 13:14.995
SHOES ON.
[ Serena ]
I'M ALMOST READY.

13:44.757 --> 13:48.328
[ Sighs ]
LET'S GO, KIDDO.
OKAY, MOMMY.

13:52.032 --> 13:54.467
[ Woman ]
WE NO LONGER OFFER THAT COURSE.

13:54.501 --> 13:56.703
YES, BUT THAT'S THE AREA
I'VE BEEN STUDYING.

13:56.736 --> 13:59.006
THAT'S MY MAJOR.
* [ Humming ]

13:59.039 --> 14:01.641
I MEAN, MY CREDITS--
I WISH I COULD HELP YOU,
MS. BROWN,

14:01.674 --> 14:03.977
BUT YOUR CREDITS ARE FROM
FOUR DIFFERENT COLLEGES.

14:04.011 --> 14:09.482
AND I HATE TO ADMIT THIS, BUT
THIS IS THE ONLY COMMUNICATIONS
CLASS WE HAVE A SPOT IN.

14:09.516 --> 14:11.484
NEWSWRITING 101?
THAT'S RIGHT.

14:11.518 --> 14:14.321
I'VE TAKEN IT.
SERENA, GET OFF THAT CHAIR.

14:14.354 --> 14:19.092
-PUBLIC SPEAKING-- IS THAT OPEN?
-THE WOMAN WHO TAUGHT THAT,
HER HUSBAND WAS TRANSFERRED.

14:19.126 --> 14:21.761
YOU PICK THOSE UP RIGHT NOW,
YOUNG LADY.

14:21.794 --> 14:24.664
CREATIVE WRITING?
I'M SORRY, NO.

14:24.697 --> 14:27.367
JUST WHAT ELSE
IS AVAILABLE?

14:27.400 --> 14:29.602
UM--
OW!

14:29.636 --> 14:33.073
TUESDAYS AND THURSDAYS
WE HAVE OPENINGS IN...

14:33.106 --> 14:36.009
BEGINNING COMPUTERS
AND MILITARY HISTORY.

14:36.043 --> 14:38.845
OH, UH, WE HAVE AN OPENING
IN HOME ECONOMICS.

14:38.878 --> 14:42.082
IT'S ONLY TWO CREDITS.
BUT MANY OF
THE MILITARY WOMEN--

14:42.115 --> 14:45.452
LIKE TO BETTER THEMSELVES
BY MAKING PIES?

14:56.829 --> 15:01.001
[ Sirens Wailing In Distance ]

15:11.111 --> 15:14.114
FEEL FREE TO GIVE THAT BACK
TO THE AGENCY WITH MY REGARDS.

15:16.649 --> 15:18.618
GOOD TO HAVE YOU HOME.

15:19.819 --> 15:22.489
WILLIAMS? GREY?
BOTH SAFE. BOTH INBOUND.

15:22.522 --> 15:24.724
MACK?

15:24.757 --> 15:26.826
NO WORD,
BUT I'M NOT SHAKING.

15:26.859 --> 15:29.462
BOB BROWN?

15:29.496 --> 15:32.132
WE GOT A SCAN
OF A POLICE REPORT.

15:32.165 --> 15:34.901
INDIVIDUAL MATCHING
HIS DESCRIPTION
VIOLENTLY RESISTING ARREST.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.970
THEY'RE IN PURSUIT.

15:38.438 --> 15:40.440
THEY CATCH HIM, THEY'LL
PUT HIM ON TRIAL FOR MURDER.

15:40.473 --> 15:42.575
BETTER KNOW IT.

15:42.609 --> 15:46.146
[ Sighs ]
[ Slaps Paper ]

15:46.179 --> 15:51.318
[ Church Bells Toll ]

16:02.895 --> 16:06.133
SO IT'S NOT BRIAN.
I JUST TALKED TO HIS MOTHER.

16:06.166 --> 16:08.635
SHE SAYS
BETSY BROKE UP WITH HIM.

16:08.668 --> 16:11.204
YOU CHECKED THAT WITH BRIAN?
YES.

16:11.238 --> 16:14.041
HOPING FOR A DIFFERENT ANSWER.

16:14.074 --> 16:16.143
SO SHE LIED TO TIFFY.
YES, SHE DID.

16:16.176 --> 16:19.779
AND HER ADVISER SAYS
HER GRADES ARE FINE.

16:19.812 --> 16:22.382
ATTENDANCE IS FINE.

16:23.816 --> 16:25.885
THEN IT'S NOT ABOUT COLLEGE.
YOU GONNA TALK TO HER?

16:25.918 --> 16:28.788
SAID SHE'D TALK TO ME.
I IMAGINE THAT'S WHAT SHE'LL DO.

16:28.821 --> 16:31.658
AND YOU'LL DADDY HER UP,
BUT YOU WON'T PUT IT TO HER.
[ Microwave Beeping ]

16:31.691 --> 16:34.361
DON'T TELL ME WHAT I'M GONNA DO.

16:34.394 --> 16:36.563
THEN SHOW ME
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO.

16:36.596 --> 16:40.500
BE CAREFUL.
EVEN THE DUMBEST OF GENERALS
WOULDN'T START A TWO-FRONT WAR.

16:42.102 --> 16:44.071
HOW MANY YOU THINK?

16:44.104 --> 16:46.339
SHE BRING LAUNDRY?

16:46.373 --> 16:48.675
- MM-HMM.
- SET THE THREE.

16:48.708 --> 16:50.543
[ Cell Phone Beeps ]

16:52.412 --> 16:54.381
GO FOR BLANE.

16:54.414 --> 16:57.016
[ Bell Tone ]

16:57.050 --> 17:01.454
[ Woman On P.A.
Speaking Spanish ]

17:04.924 --> 17:07.260
[ Chattering In Spanish ]

17:12.365 --> 17:14.767
[ Ship Horn Blows
In Distance ]

17:55.575 --> 17:58.478
[ Shouts In Spanish ]

17:59.779 --> 18:03.082
[ Men Shouting In Spanish ]

18:14.461 --> 18:16.929
[ Man ]
I DON'T UNDERSTAND!

18:16.963 --> 18:20.667
- [ Speaking Spanish ]
- [ Man ]
IT'S NOT MY GUN!

18:23.970 --> 18:25.805
[ Bell Tone ]

18:28.175 --> 18:30.410
¡SEÑOR!

18:30.443 --> 18:34.314
[ Woman On P.A. ]
FOR SECURITY REASONS, THE FERRY
TO IBIZA HAS BEEN DELAYED.

18:34.347 --> 18:37.617
PLEASE STAND BY.
[ Continues In Spanish ]

18:53.065 --> 18:56.969
IT'S FREAKY, HUH?
[ Chuckles ]
YEAH.

18:59.739 --> 19:02.108
I GUESS, UH--
I GUESS WE MISSED THE BOAT.

19:02.141 --> 19:04.677
I GUESS.

19:04.711 --> 19:07.447
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE IT'S FATE.

19:07.480 --> 19:09.316
GETTING STRANDED
IN A FOREIGN COUNTRY,

19:09.349 --> 19:13.653
TALKING TO SOMEONE
YOU'D PROBABLY JUST
WALK RIGHT BY BACK HOME.

19:17.056 --> 19:19.559
WELL, WHAT ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO NOW?

19:21.861 --> 19:24.497
CAN I ASK YOU SOMETHING?
SURE.

19:24.531 --> 19:27.033
WHERE'D YOU GET YOUR DRUGS?

19:27.066 --> 19:29.035
HOW COULD YOU TELL?

19:29.068 --> 19:31.738
[ Alarm Bell Rings ]

19:38.211 --> 19:40.880
KIERAN, YOU HAVE DETENTION
IN FIVE MINUTES.
WE HAVE TIME.

19:42.215 --> 19:45.418
THANKS.

19:45.452 --> 19:47.820
- BONNIE, WHAT'S UP WITH YOU?
- TEENAGE REBELLION?

19:47.854 --> 19:50.490
THERE'S REBELLION,
AND THERE'S STUPID.

19:50.523 --> 19:52.559
KIDDO, DON'T BE STUPID.

20:18.551 --> 20:21.254
YOU LOOK LIKE
THE CHESHIRE CAT.

20:21.288 --> 20:24.724
WELL, I DISAPPEAR
AND REAPPEAR AND DISAPPEAR.

20:24.757 --> 20:26.626
COME HERE.
YOU'RE TWO MINUTES LATE.

20:28.395 --> 20:31.798
AND YOU'RE ACTUALLY ON TIME.

20:35.001 --> 20:38.805
[ Sighs ]

20:43.175 --> 20:45.278
THAT'S FOR YOU.

20:45.312 --> 20:48.648
AND SO ARE THESE.

20:48.681 --> 20:51.684
I KNOW YOU CAN'T TAKE 'EM HOME
AND PUT 'EM IN A VASE, BUT--

20:56.289 --> 20:58.057
IS THIS ABOUT MACK?

20:58.090 --> 21:00.059
HE'S NOT--

21:00.092 --> 21:03.129
NO.

21:03.162 --> 21:06.333
BUT YOU KNOW
WHERE HE IS?
NO.

21:06.366 --> 21:08.635
WE HAVEN'T HEARD ANYTHING
TO MAKE US THINK
THERE'S A PROBLEM.

21:08.668 --> 21:11.471
- BUT HE IS MISSING?
- HE'S LATE.

21:11.504 --> 21:14.173
AND I WANTED YOU
TO BE AWARE THAT--

21:14.206 --> 21:16.843
I KNOW YOU ARE.
THE REST OF THE TEAM?

21:16.876 --> 21:19.512
SOME ARE IN OR INCOMING.
BUT TWO ARE--

21:19.546 --> 21:22.882
- LATE.
- AS YOU SAY.

21:28.187 --> 21:30.222
[ Sighs ]

21:37.530 --> 21:40.299
[ Woman ]
OH, OKAY.
COME ON.

21:40.333 --> 21:42.168
[ Chuckling ]

21:42.201 --> 21:44.871
[ Williams ]
I SWEAR. I USED TO
CARRY IT ALL THE TIME.

21:44.904 --> 21:47.674
GENTLEMEN... AND LADY.

21:47.707 --> 21:49.809
HEY, MOST LOVELY
MRS. BROWN.

21:49.842 --> 21:51.978
AND LITTLE "BROWNLING."

21:52.011 --> 21:54.714
- MISS SERENA BROWN.
- PLEASED TO MEET YOU, SERENA.

21:54.747 --> 21:56.883
NICE TO MEET YOU TOO.

21:56.916 --> 22:00.820
LAURENDA GEORGE, A GOOD FRIEND.
KIM BROWN, WIFE OF A COWORKER.
VERY NICE TO MEET YOU.

22:00.853 --> 22:03.990
- NICE TO MEET YOU TOO.
- THAT WHAT YOU'RE
CALLING ME NOW? A FRIEND?

22:04.023 --> 22:06.292
- I SAID A GOOD FRIEND, BABY.
- [ Chuckles ]

22:06.325 --> 22:10.630
- [ Chuckles ]
WE SHOULD GET MOVING.
- GUYS, IS BOB OFF DUTY TOO?

22:10.663 --> 22:11.898
- OUT OF THE OFFICE.
- YEAH, BUT--

22:11.931 --> 22:14.367
- IT WAS GOOD SEEING YOU.
- YES, BUT LISTEN--

22:14.401 --> 22:16.503
IF I SEE BOB,
I'LL TELL HIM, CALL YOU.
OKAY, BUT--

22:16.536 --> 22:18.971
BUT--
WE'LL SEE YOU LATER, KIM.

22:19.005 --> 22:21.107
ALL RIGHT.
[ Car Starts ]

22:37.056 --> 22:40.326
- WE'VE BEEN WAITING ON YOU.
- I WAS AT AUNT TIFFY'S
BABYSITTING.

22:40.359 --> 22:43.430
YOU BACK-TALK YOUR MOTHER,
TOLD HER YOU WERE HOME
TO TALK TO ME.

22:43.463 --> 22:47.900
I COME HOME.
YOU'RE NOT HERE.
WHAT DO I MAKE OF THIS?

22:47.934 --> 22:50.903
- YOU BREAK THAT SIDE WINDOW?
- I FORGOT MY KEY.
NOBODY WAS HERE.

22:50.937 --> 22:52.905
IT WAS COLD.
MM-HMM.

22:52.939 --> 22:55.442
TIFFY HAS A KEY.
YOU COULD'VE GONE THERE.

22:55.475 --> 22:57.744
BUT YOU CHOSE
TO DESTROY PROPERTY.

22:57.777 --> 23:00.547
YOU THINK THAT'S NORMAL?

23:03.716 --> 23:05.852
YOUR MOTHER WAS CONCERNED
THAT YOU MIGHT USE THIS.

23:05.885 --> 23:08.955
I WASN'T GONNA USE THE GUN,
DADDY.

23:12.158 --> 23:14.727
OKAY THEN.

23:16.128 --> 23:19.298
OH. MMM.

23:21.067 --> 23:24.403
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

23:24.437 --> 23:27.740
I NEED MY BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

23:27.774 --> 23:30.209
YOU DON'T NEED THAT
TO GET A JOB.
A JOB?

23:30.242 --> 23:33.145
WELL, YOU DROP OUT OF SCHOOL,
YOU GOTTA SUPPORT YOURSELF.

23:33.179 --> 23:35.482
I PRESUME YOU'RE PLANNING
ON GETTING A JOB.

23:35.515 --> 23:38.818
LOOKIT, I'M NOT IN
THE RIGHT PLACE AT SCHOOL.
I'M NOT CUT OUT FOR IT.

23:38.851 --> 23:42.421
LIKE I SAID, YOU DON'T NEED
A BIRTH CERTIFICATE
TO PROCURE EMPLOYMENT.

23:42.455 --> 23:45.324
I NEED IT TO ENLIST.

23:59.806 --> 24:02.274
THE AUSTRALIAN GUY
OVER THERE.

24:04.644 --> 24:08.848
GREAT.
HOW MUCH YOU GOT?

24:08.881 --> 24:11.250
WHAT? YOU MEAN--
CASH, ON YOU.

24:11.283 --> 24:14.120
JUST TO GET US STARTED.

24:20.960 --> 24:24.330
I GOT A FRIEND BACK HOME
WANTED ME TO BUY HIM A GUITAR.

24:25.464 --> 24:27.900
WELL, THIS'LL BE MORE FUN.

24:30.469 --> 24:33.039
WAIT HERE.

24:45.151 --> 24:47.153
HEY.
HEY.

24:47.186 --> 24:49.689
ME AND A BUNCH OF FRIENDS
ARE HAVING A PARTY.

24:49.722 --> 24:52.191
GOOD ON YA.
YEAH.

24:52.224 --> 24:54.861
WELL, WE FIGURE
WE CAN USE A LITTLE HELP.

24:54.894 --> 24:56.996
YEAH?
YEAH.

24:57.029 --> 24:59.632
HOW MUCH WOULD
2,000 EUROS BUY US?

24:59.666 --> 25:01.968
THAT IS, IF YOU GOT IT.

25:02.001 --> 25:04.103
I CAN GET IT.

25:05.037 --> 25:07.273
I'M WAITING.

25:37.469 --> 25:39.538
[ Gasps ]

25:54.120 --> 25:56.488
[ Helicopters Whirring
In Distance ]

26:02.662 --> 26:05.431
[ Sighs ]

26:05.464 --> 26:07.299
DID YOU HAVE ANY TROUBLE?

26:09.335 --> 26:11.137
RIGHT AS RAIN.

26:14.573 --> 26:18.277
[ Sighs ]
AREN'T YOU EVER SCARED
OUT THERE?

26:18.310 --> 26:20.312
SCARED OF LOSING EVERYTHING?

26:22.314 --> 26:24.250
LOSING ME?

26:31.123 --> 26:36.195
YOU... ARE WHAT
GETS ME HOME, BABY.

26:42.434 --> 26:45.504
WE SAID FOUR YEARS OF COLLEGE,
AND THAT'S WHAT WE MEANT.

26:45.537 --> 26:47.473
FOUR YEARS.

26:47.506 --> 26:50.009
- OF BEING UNHAPPY.
- OF BEING IN COLLEGE.

26:50.042 --> 26:53.079
YOU DIDN'T GO TO COLLEGE.
I LEARNED SOMEWHERE ELSE.

26:53.112 --> 26:56.148
AND THAT'S WHAT I WANT.
IN THE MILITARY,
I'LL LEARN SKILLS.

26:56.182 --> 26:58.350
THEY'LL GET ME A GOOD JOB
AFTER, WHEN I'M DONE.

26:58.384 --> 27:00.486
THERE'S MONEY
FOR SCHOOL AFTER.

27:00.519 --> 27:02.689
THERE'S DISCRIMINATION
AGAINST WOMEN.

27:02.722 --> 27:06.859
THERE'S MUD AND DIRT.
THERE'S RAPE. THERE'S WAR.
I KNOW THE MILITARY LIFE.

27:06.893 --> 27:09.762
IS THAT RIGHT?
IT'S BEEN ALL MY LIFE.

27:09.796 --> 27:11.964
I DON'T THINK THE MILITARY
IS THE ISSUE.

27:11.998 --> 27:15.501
WOULD IT SURPRISE YOU TO KNOW
THAT YOU'RE NOT INVOLVED
IN THIS DECISION?

27:15.534 --> 27:18.004
IT SURPRISES ME, YOUNG LADY.

27:18.037 --> 27:20.707
WHEN YOU SPEAK TO YOUR MOTHER,
YOU DO IT WITH RESPECT.

27:22.041 --> 27:24.043
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME?
YES, SIR.

27:24.076 --> 27:27.146
[ Knocking ]

27:31.350 --> 27:34.687
[ Knocking ]

27:35.855 --> 27:38.090
HEY, KIM.
HI.

27:41.093 --> 27:44.831
I CAN COME BACK LATER.
NO, NO. IT'S OKAY.
COME ON IN.

27:44.864 --> 27:47.133
NO.
I SHOULD GET BACK.

27:47.166 --> 27:49.368
- KIM, IS THERE ANYTHING--
- NO.

27:49.401 --> 27:51.537
THIS IS OUR DAUGHTER,
BETSY. BETSY?

27:51.570 --> 27:55.141
THIS IS MRS. BROWN-- KIM.
HI.

27:55.174 --> 27:57.844
SHE'S MARRIED TO
ONE OF MY--
HIS MEN. BOB.

27:57.877 --> 28:00.980
TO BOB.
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU.

28:01.013 --> 28:04.350
I'M SURE I'LL SEE YOU AROUND.
I ONLY CAME BY TO GET SOME--

28:06.953 --> 28:10.356
NEVER MIND.
I SHOULD GET GOING.

28:10.389 --> 28:12.224
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

28:14.460 --> 28:16.295
[ Cell Phone Rings ]

28:20.199 --> 28:23.369
MACK'S HOME.

28:24.603 --> 28:27.206
- [ Sighs ]
WE'LL FINISH THIS LATER.
- YOUR WAY.

28:27.239 --> 28:29.776
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER.

28:29.809 --> 28:32.278
YOU WOULDN'T TRY TO STOP ME
IF I WAS YOUR SON.

28:36.648 --> 28:39.285
YOU'RE NOT MY SON.

28:39.318 --> 28:41.954
YOU'RE MY DAUGHTER.

28:43.289 --> 28:46.358
I APOLOGIZE FOR MY BEHAVIOR
WHEN I CAME HOME.

28:46.392 --> 28:49.862
I HEARD WHAT YOU HAD TO SAY,
AND I WAS OUT OF LINE,
AND I'M SORRY.

28:49.896 --> 28:52.799
BUT I'M AN ADULT NOW.

28:52.832 --> 28:55.634
AND I NEED TO MAKE
MY OWN DECISIONS, EVEN
IF THEY'RE THE WRONG ONES.

28:55.667 --> 28:57.870
WELL, THAT'S BETTER.

28:57.904 --> 29:01.240
AND AS AN ADULT, I'D LIKE
MY BIRTH CERTIFICATE, PLEASE.

29:07.914 --> 29:10.917
[ Dog Barking In Distance ]

29:16.455 --> 29:20.092
[ Man Speaking Spanish ]

29:25.164 --> 29:27.133
OKAY, OKAY.
HI.

29:27.166 --> 29:30.169
ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, I FOLLOWED YOU.
BLOODY HELL!

29:30.202 --> 29:33.272
I WANT TO MEET THE MAN WHO
SUPPLIES YOU. I'VE GOT $1,000
FOR THE MAN WITH THE BOAT.

29:33.305 --> 29:35.975
- A BOAT?
- I NEED A BOAT, YEAH.

29:37.276 --> 29:40.246
WHY WE NOT KILL YOU NOW
AND TAKE YOUR MONEY?

29:40.279 --> 29:42.314
GIVE IT A SHOT.

29:45.284 --> 29:49.555
* [ R&B ]

29:52.391 --> 29:55.828
CAN WE TALK?

29:55.862 --> 29:57.830
I DON'T KNOW. CAN WE?

29:57.864 --> 30:00.632
LET'S START THIS VISIT OVER.

30:00.666 --> 30:04.203
I'LL ACKNOWLEDGE THAT YOU
AREN'T A LITTLE GIRL ANYMORE.
IT DOESN'T FEEL THAT WAY.

30:04.236 --> 30:06.638
WE'RE PARENTS.

30:06.672 --> 30:10.376
AS A PARENT,
I'D LIKE TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT THIS HAS ALL MEANT.

30:10.409 --> 30:13.245
JUST MEANS THAT
I'VE GROWN UP.
YES, YOU HAVE.

30:14.480 --> 30:16.382
BUT WHAT'S EATING AWAY AT YOU?

30:17.984 --> 30:21.888
EVERYTHING'S CHANGING.
THAT'S ALL.
YOU WON'T UNDERSTAND.

30:21.921 --> 30:25.657
WHEN I WAS YOUNG,
I DIDN'T THINK MY PARENTS
UNDERSTOOD A THING I DID.

30:25.691 --> 30:29.461
- WELL, THAT WAS YOU.
- THERE WAS A BOY.

30:29.495 --> 30:31.663
JAY HOWARD ALEXANDER.

30:31.697 --> 30:35.868
I DROPPED OUT OF SCHOOL.
I FOLLOWED THAT BOY TO CHICAGO.

30:35.902 --> 30:38.370
I GOT OFF AT UNION STATION.
I KNEW RIGHT THEN
I HAD MADE A MISTAKE.

30:38.404 --> 30:41.840
BUT DAMNED IF I WAS
GOING TO ADMIT THAT TO
MY FOLKS, SO I STAYED.

30:41.874 --> 30:45.677
WELL, IT WAS YOUR DECISION.
IT WAS RIGHT FOR YOU.

30:45.711 --> 30:47.746
I MISSED A SEMESTER.

30:47.779 --> 30:49.581
I MISSED MY FOLKS.

30:51.050 --> 30:53.986
LUCKILY,
I NEVER MISSED A PERIOD.

30:54.020 --> 30:57.223
WELL, THIS ISN'T
ABOUT A BOY.

30:57.256 --> 31:00.026
THAT'S RIGHT.
IT'S ABOUT A MAN,
YOUR FATHER.

31:01.593 --> 31:04.096
YOU WANT TO BE LIKE HIM,
SO YOU DON'T HAVE TO
BE LIKE ME.

31:04.130 --> 31:08.434
I WANT A LIFE THAT
I'M RESPONSIBLE FOR.

31:08.467 --> 31:10.702
I WANT A LIFE THAT I RUN.

31:10.736 --> 31:13.572
I MEAN,

31:13.605 --> 31:15.407
WHERE'S YOUR LIFE?

31:18.978 --> 31:21.981
IN YOU, BIRD.

31:29.621 --> 31:31.991
YOU KNOW HOW TO HOLD IT.
YOU KNOW HOW TO CHECK IT.

31:33.960 --> 31:36.395
[ Gun Clicks ]

31:38.430 --> 31:40.666
[ Closes Chamber ]

31:46.939 --> 31:48.975
GET YOUR COAT.

31:49.008 --> 31:51.677
WE WON'T BE LONG.

31:54.346 --> 31:56.448
[ Gunshots ]

31:56.482 --> 32:00.719
YOU'RE RUSTY.
I DON'T DO THIS
ALL THE TIME.

32:00.752 --> 32:04.423
MY POINT.
[ Machine Gun Fire
In Distance ]

32:04.456 --> 32:06.292
I'VE PAID MY DUES
FOR THIS FAMILY.

32:06.325 --> 32:10.096
I HAVEN'T PAID MINE.

32:10.129 --> 32:11.964
WE'RE ALL PAID UP.
[ Machine Gun Fire Continues ]

32:14.666 --> 32:17.069
THIS AIN'T NO VIDEO GAME.
I KNOW.

32:17.103 --> 32:19.105
[ Helicopter Whirs ]
YOU KNOW?

32:19.138 --> 32:21.840
HOW IS IT YOU KNOW?

32:21.873 --> 32:24.310
MY JOB DON'T GOT NO
"TAKE YOUR DAUGHTER
TO WORK DAY."

32:26.278 --> 32:28.447
[ Machine Gun Fire Continues ]

32:28.480 --> 32:30.616
BUT I WANT TO BE ABLE
TO GO OUT AND DO--
YOU WANT TO FIGHT?

32:32.384 --> 32:35.387
- WHO ARE YOU MAD AT?
- [ Sighs ]

32:36.288 --> 32:39.125
I'M NOT MAD.

32:39.158 --> 32:42.494
I JUST...
WANT TO GET OUT THERE.
IT'S NEVER GONNA HAPPEN FOR YOU.

32:42.528 --> 32:45.164
SURE, IT WILL.
[ Clip Clicks ]

32:52.671 --> 32:54.640
FORGET THE SIGHTS.
LOOK AT THE TARGET.

33:00.012 --> 33:03.415
- SO IF I WAS A BOY--
- I'D TELL YOU
TO JOIN THE R.O.T.C.

33:06.085 --> 33:08.887
I'M NOT SAYING YOU'RE WRONG.
I'M SAYING YOU
GOTTA HAVE OPTIONS.

33:08.920 --> 33:13.025
FINISH SCHOOL, GRADUATE.

33:13.059 --> 33:15.494
YOU STILL WANT TO DO THIS,
I'LL SELL YOU YOUR FIRST SALUTE.

33:17.263 --> 33:19.531
HOW ABOUT IT?

33:25.437 --> 33:27.506
WHAT ARE YOU SCARED OF?

33:27.539 --> 33:29.875
I FEAR NO MAN.

33:30.942 --> 33:34.246
ONE WOMAN.

33:34.280 --> 33:39.285
COURAGE IS MOVING INTO DANGER
WHEN THERE'S A MEANS OF ESCAPE.

33:42.354 --> 33:46.258
YOU GOT CHOICES, BETS.
BE COURAGEOUS.

33:46.292 --> 33:49.661
I'LL TRY.
"I'LL TRY" MEANS "I'LL FAIL."

33:49.695 --> 33:52.264
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT,
YOU DON'T BELONG IN THE ARMY.

33:52.298 --> 33:54.133
[ Machine Gun Fire
In Distance ]

33:58.470 --> 34:01.440
GOOD WORK.
WE'RE DONE HERE.

34:04.076 --> 34:07.446
[ Chattering ]
* [ Soft Rock ]

34:11.717 --> 34:13.952
YOU SURE THIS IS THE PLACE?
HE'LL COME.

34:16.122 --> 34:18.390
DOS CERVEZAS.

34:21.793 --> 34:24.596
* [ Singing In Spanish ]

34:29.000 --> 34:31.303
GRACIAS.

34:33.339 --> 34:35.207
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

34:35.241 --> 34:37.109
GRACIAS.
[ Man ]
HOLA.

34:37.143 --> 34:40.612
- HOLA.
- RUM.

34:42.648 --> 34:44.550
[ Speaks Spanish ]

34:44.583 --> 34:47.219
MY ENGLISH IS PERFECT.
I CAN PAY.

34:47.253 --> 34:49.221
A THOUSAND.
[ Chuckles ]

34:49.255 --> 34:51.323
FOR A THOUSAND, YOU CAN'T
EVEN LOOK AT THE BOAT.

34:51.357 --> 34:53.559
SO HOW MUCH?

34:53.592 --> 34:56.995
FOR AN AMERICAN--
AND AN ASSASSIN?

34:57.028 --> 35:01.500
[ Speaks Spanish ]
THEY SAY ANYONE
WHO GIVES YOU UP GETS 10,000.

35:03.635 --> 35:07.939
YOU KNOW, IF I WAS
IN YOUR LINE OF WORK,

35:07.973 --> 35:10.609
I'D WANT TO BE ABLE
TO SEE AT NIGHT BEFORE
OTHER PEOPLE COULD SEE ME.

35:12.611 --> 35:15.113
NO. FOR 10,000, YOU--
YOU CAN'T EVEN TOUCH IT.

35:15.147 --> 35:18.984
BUT FOR A BOAT RIDE,
20 MAG INFRARED NIGHTSCOPE.

35:19.017 --> 35:22.854
VERY LIMITED ISSUE,
U.S. MILITARY ONLY,
HALF-KILOMETER RANGE.

35:22.888 --> 35:24.990
ATENCIÓN.

35:25.023 --> 35:27.526
YOU!

35:27.559 --> 35:29.828
[ Sniffling ]
WHERE DID YOU GO?

35:29.861 --> 35:32.298
WITH MY MONEY?
SHE JUST WANTS
HER MONEY BACK, MATE.

35:32.331 --> 35:36.702
[ Speaking Spanish ]
YOU'RE SPEAKING TOO FAST.

35:36.735 --> 35:38.770
WHAT'S GOING ON?
SPEAK ENGLISH!

35:38.804 --> 35:42.708
[ Continues
Speaking Spanish ]

35:42.741 --> 35:45.844
COME WITH ME
IF YOU PLEASE, MISS.
HEY!

35:45.877 --> 35:48.480
HEY.
[ Woman, Indistinct ]

35:48.514 --> 35:51.450
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME.
STOP IT!

35:51.483 --> 35:54.820
WHAT'S GOING ON?
LEAVE ME ALONE!
LET HER GO.

35:54.853 --> 35:56.655
SHE'S MY CONCERN NOW.

35:56.688 --> 35:58.657
CONSIDER HER
PART OF YOUR PAYMENT.
OH, MY GOD!

35:58.690 --> 36:01.059
- NO. THAT'S NOT GONNA WORK.
- [ Gasps ]

36:05.231 --> 36:07.399
[ Woman ]
OH, MY GOD.

36:07.433 --> 36:10.068
THANK YOU.

36:16.342 --> 36:18.109
LET'S TAKE A STROLL.

36:20.246 --> 36:23.415
I KNOW EVERYONE'S BACK
BUT BOB.

36:23.449 --> 36:28.220
LISTEN, WHEN YOU CAME OVER,
WE WERE RIGHT
IN THE MIDDLE OF--

36:28.254 --> 36:31.757
WELL, WE JUST WERE.
I WANTED TO COME OVER
AND TALK TO YOU ABOUT THAT.

36:31.790 --> 36:34.426
IF BOB WAS IN TROUBLE,
WOULD YOU TELL ME?

36:34.460 --> 36:36.728
NO.

36:37.563 --> 36:40.532
IF HE WAS ALL RIGHT?
YES.

36:40.566 --> 36:45.170
SO YOU'RE SAYIN'...
HE'S IN TROUBLE?

36:45.203 --> 36:48.139
THE BEST TRAINING
A MAN CAN HAVE
IS WHAT YOUR HUSBAND HAS.

36:49.575 --> 36:51.743
BOB KNOWS
WHAT HE'S DOING.

36:51.777 --> 36:54.446
YOU JUST HAVE TO HAVE FAITH
IN JUST HOW GOOD HE IS.
YOU FOLLOW?

36:56.047 --> 36:58.016
YOU HAVE TO BELIEVE
AS HE HAS TO BELIEVE,

36:58.049 --> 37:01.186
TO KNOW THAT YOU'RE
AT HOME HANDLING THINGS,

37:01.219 --> 37:03.755
LIVING YOUR LIFE
THE BEST YOU CAN.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.997
ALL RIGHT THEN.

37:22.073 --> 37:24.743
[ Chattering ]

37:24.776 --> 37:28.146
MILITARY HISTORY.
THERE STILL AN OPENING?

37:28.179 --> 37:30.649
I BELIEVE SO, YES.
SIGN ME UP...
BEFORE I CHANGE MY MIND.

37:30.682 --> 37:33.552
WONDERFUL.

37:33.585 --> 37:36.221
YOU COULD TAKE ME WITH YOU,
WHEREVER YOU GO.

37:36.254 --> 37:38.123
OH, YOU POOR THING.
UH, COULD YOU NOT?

37:38.156 --> 37:41.793
[ Clears Throat ] UH,
THE BARMAN'S CALLING THE POLICE.
NO.

37:41.827 --> 37:45.063
I REALLY MUST GO.
I CAN'T AFFORD THE PUBLICITY.

37:45.096 --> 37:47.966
- I'M NOT EVEN SUPPOSED
TO BE IN THIS COUNTRY.
- WAIT, WAIT!

37:47.999 --> 37:52.471
AY! WHY YOU DO THIS THING?
HE WAS GOING TO TAKE ME
WITH HIM ON HIS YACHT.

37:52.504 --> 37:55.006
- HIS WHAT?
- HIS RICH, BIG BEAUTIFUL BOAT!

37:55.040 --> 37:57.776
- A YACHT?
- SÍ, HIS YACHT.

38:00.612 --> 38:02.948
WHOA. WHERE-WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?
LOOK. I REALLY LIKE YOU, UM--

38:02.981 --> 38:05.951
JANICE.
YEAH, JANICE.
BUT I--

38:05.984 --> 38:08.320
WHAT?
YOU HAVE A GIRLFRIEND NOW?
NO. I'M GAY.

38:10.188 --> 38:12.391
YOU DROPPED THIS.

38:17.496 --> 38:19.531
THAT'S MY HANDKERCHIEF!

38:22.968 --> 38:25.604
WHY?

38:25.637 --> 38:29.107
WHY ARE YOU
PICKING THAT TRASH
WHEN YOU COULD HAVE ME?

38:29.140 --> 38:31.142
[ Ship Horn Blows ]
TRASH? YOU--

38:35.146 --> 38:37.516
[ Grunts, Groans ]

38:37.549 --> 38:39.551
WELL!

38:39.585 --> 38:41.853
PERMISSION TO BOARD, SIR?

38:41.887 --> 38:45.991
[ Sirens Wailing,
Tires Squealing ]

38:58.704 --> 39:00.706
YOU FOUND IT.
WHAT?

39:00.739 --> 39:03.208
YOUR GRANDMAMA'S RING.

39:03.241 --> 39:06.044
OH. IT WAS
IN THE DRAWER OF MY DESK.

39:06.077 --> 39:08.380
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR IT FOR--
ME TOO.

39:08.414 --> 39:12.350
JANUARY BABY.
GARNET.

39:12.384 --> 39:16.254
IT'S A LITTLE BIT
OF A STONE. BUT IT'S BEEN
IN OUR FAMILY FOR SO LONG.

39:16.287 --> 39:18.524
WHAT'S THIS?

39:18.557 --> 39:20.325
YOUR BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

39:20.358 --> 39:23.595
MAKE SURE YOU PUT IT
SOMEPLACE WHERE YOU REMEMBER...

39:23.629 --> 39:25.597
IN CASE YOU NEED
THE DAMN THING FOR SOMETHING.

39:25.631 --> 39:28.434
I DON'T NEED IT.
I REMEMBER YOU WERE BORN.

39:28.467 --> 39:31.970
[ Engine Starts ]

39:39.144 --> 39:41.312
[ Brakes Squeak ]

39:45.984 --> 39:49.054
I'M SCARED.
THAT'S WHAT IT IS.

39:49.087 --> 39:53.525
[ Crying ]
WE'RE ALL SCARED.
HONEY--

39:53.559 --> 39:56.261
THIS PLACE. THIS--
IT'S HOME.

39:56.294 --> 39:59.030
IT'S WHAT I KNOW.
THE RULES ARE DIFFERENT
AT SCHOOL.

39:59.064 --> 40:02.400
MOM, THE WAY PEOPLE ACT--
I AM NOT READY.
TRUST ME.

40:02.434 --> 40:05.904
THE ARMY ISN'T
WHAT YOU THINK EITHER.
THEN I'VE GOT NO PLACE TO GO!

40:05.937 --> 40:09.140
YOU GOT A LIFE AT SCHOOL.
YOU JUST GOTTA START IT.
BUT WHAT IF I CAN'T?

40:09.174 --> 40:12.110
THIS PLACE
IS GONNA BE HERE.

40:13.244 --> 40:16.314
OUR HOUSE, THE BASE.

40:16.347 --> 40:21.119
MOST IMPORTANT,
YOUR DADDY AND ME,
WE'RE ALWAYS GONNA BE HERE.

40:26.658 --> 40:29.995
[ Sniffling ]

40:36.201 --> 40:38.303
I'M PROUD OF YOU, BIRD.

40:38.336 --> 40:41.106
THANK YOU, MOM.

40:45.310 --> 40:47.779
[ Engine Starts ]
CALL US.

40:59.457 --> 41:02.460
[ Vehicle Approaches ]

41:04.663 --> 41:07.065
[ Engine Revs, Stops ]

41:17.743 --> 41:21.012
THEY COME AND THEY GO.

41:24.850 --> 41:28.319
[ Laughing ]
IT TURNS OUT THAT
SHE WAS ROMANIAN.

41:28.353 --> 41:32.791
SHE WAS WORKING IN THE HOTEL
AS AN ILLEGAL.
[ Laughs ]

41:32.824 --> 41:34.860
SAYS SHE'LL GET ME OUT
THE SAME WAY SHE CAME IN.

41:34.893 --> 41:38.864
I RIDE ACROSS THE BORDER
IN HER COUSIN'S CHICKEN TRUCK.

41:38.897 --> 41:42.000
[ Men Laughing ]

41:42.033 --> 41:44.936
IT'S EASIER TO STEAL A PLANE.

41:46.071 --> 41:49.908
YO, YO,
I WAS LAND, REMEMBER?

41:49.941 --> 41:53.679
[ Laughing ]
OKAY, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
HOLD ON A SECOND. BOB--

41:53.712 --> 41:56.882
BOB, YOU'RE TELLIN' ME
THAT YOU DENY YOURSELF...

41:56.915 --> 42:00.085
A NIGHT WITH A GORGEOUS,
AVAILABLE HIPPIE CHICK?

42:00.118 --> 42:02.320
MMM.
I DON'T KNOW.
I GUESS I BELIEVE THAT.

42:02.353 --> 42:04.222
HE'S MARRIED.

42:04.255 --> 42:07.192
[ Mack And Grey ]
NOT OVERSEAS!
[ Laughing ]

42:08.727 --> 42:11.262
OKAY. LISTEN, BOB.
I'M WITH YOU RIGHT
UP TO THAT POINT.

42:11.296 --> 42:13.932
BUT THEN YOU TELL ME YOU MEET
THIS ENGLISH GUY WITH A YACHT?

42:13.965 --> 42:17.936
RUPERT.
[ Grey Chuckles ]

42:21.206 --> 42:24.542
- AND HE JUST TAKES YOU WITH?
- MM-HMM.

42:25.977 --> 42:28.179
WHAT'S HE LEAVING OUT?

42:28.213 --> 42:30.115
